title: For Sale:  Sharps 1863 50-70 Conversion Carbine Military SRC
location: New Hampshire, New Hampshire, United States
postcontent: Nice Conversion Sharps 1863 Carbine in 50-70. The Sharps is in NRA good condition. This SRC sports the standard 22" round barrel. To start on the condition, the wood is your average military used type with normal bumps and bruises. There are no cracks or major issues with them. The correct cartouche is present on the left wrist under the saddle ring bar. The wood fit is good. The stocks are the correct dark reddish tone. The metal finish on the gun is nice and honest,this rifle has a very nice look. The proper proof stampings are present on the frame on the left and right side. The front sight is a correct and original Sharps blade and the rear sight is a RS Lawrence Sharps ladder type. All markings such as serial number, barrel markings are correct and show well. The function and mechanics of this gun are excellent. The hammer notches hold firm in both 1/2 and full extension. The action cycles smoothly and the lock up is tight. The screws are all servicable and appear they have not been removed in decades. The barrel band has a crack at the top, but it fits fine and tight. The bore is good with normal rifling and some light pitting. Should shoot just fine with old cowboy loads. Overall, in my opinion this is a good condition 1863 Sharps carbine that would make a nice collectors piece and can do shipping.

title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch VP9, FDE, Used, Three magazines
postcontent: Heckler & Koch VP9, FDE, Used, Three magazines This pistol has had 200 rounds through it and comes with three magazines and HK photo-luminescence night sights.  Buy it online at www.copsgunshop.net.  All FFL rules and regs apply.  Buyer pays shipping or sales tax.  Sorry, no trades.   Experience gained by HK engineers with the recent P30 pistol had a direct influence on the design of the VP9, but the VP9 breaks new ground with its integration of a unique striker firing system with an enhanced HK “light pull” trigger. The net result is trigger quality unequaled in any production striker fired handgun. HK pioneered the first striker fired handguns, producing both the VP70 and P7 series, designs that impacted several models by HK competitors. But a superior trigger has eluded most striker fired pistol designs. The VP9 trigger surpasses those found on competitors. It has a short, light take-up with a solid, single action type break followed by a short positive reset. The VP9 trigger has a consistent pre-travel pull with a positive wall/crisp break. Typically, striker fired guns have a pre-travel pull that increases in weight as you go through the trigger stroke. With the VP9, you have a less than noticeable pre-travel pull until the trigger reaches the engagement point of the fire control parts prior to trigger break. The VP9 uses HK’s ergonomic handgun grip design that includes three changeable backstraps and six side panels— accommodating all hand sizes. Molded finger grooves in the front of the pistol’s grip also instinctively position an operator’s hand for optimal shooting. Only HK handguns have such a customized grip. Although influenced by other HK models, the VP9 has all the hallmarks of the latest, state-of-the-art handgun. All controls are completely ambidextrous. Slide releases are present on both sides of the frame and the magazine release can be easily activated by left- or right-handed shooters. A new feature is HK’s patented charging supports — simple components that are mounted on each side of the rear of the slide and provide better gripping leverage for racking the slide rearward. The charging supports speed reloading and make operating the VP9 easier for shooters with reduced hand strength. The VP pistols uses the proven P30 steel magazine; 15 and 10-round capacity available. The VP9 has an extended Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 rail molded into its polymer frame for mounting lights and accessories. The rail has been tested and certified to handle mounted accessories up to 5.6 ounces. The VP9’s proprietary captive flat recoil spring helps reduce the recoil forces effecting the operator and the handgun, improving shooter control during rapid firing and prolonging component service life. HK’s famous cold hammer forged barrel — made from cannon grade steel — ensures long service life. Similar HK barrels on 9 mm P30 models have fired more than 90,000 rounds in endurance tests in 2010. The polygonal bore profile, with no traditional lands-and-grooves rifling, contributes to longer service life as well as a slight increase in muzzle velocity. The VP9’s machined steel slide is protected from corrosion and wear by HK’s hostile environment finish and all metal components, including springs and pins have superior metallurgy. VP pistols are made in Heckler & Koch’s Oberndorf factory in southwest Germany. The VP9 is well-suited for civilian sport shooting, security, military, and law enforcement use. Covered by Heckler & Koch’s limited lifetime warranty, the HK VP9 is a solid design engineered with the famous long-term durability that make HK products especially cost-effective when subjected to total life cycle cost analysis. Suggested retail price of the VP9 is $719. New for 2016 are Flat Dark Earth (FDE) models, VPs with special colorants added to the frame during the molding process creating the tan/brown color scheme increasing used by military and security units. The frame’s color is indestructible, permanent and completely resistant to fading or chemical change.

title: For Sale:  Custom CAI DRACO Sidefolder AK-47
postcontent: More pictures here: http://www.gunbroker.com/item/674858442You're looking at a fully custom built Romanian Draco AK-47. This started out as a pistol. From there we added an AMD barrel extension and AMD extended Fishbone muzzle break. These were threaded onto the stock barrel then pinned at the bottom to bring the barrel length to just over 16" to comply with BATFE regulations. Next we added a Stormwerkz folding stock adaptor which is attached with two bolts (and can be removed if you wish to convert this back to a pistol). This locks up tight in both positions, no wiggle in it at all!Then came the ACE 8.5" Skeleton Stock with a 1" rubber shoulder pad. We cut the front sight rings and converted it to a moon shape (like other AK's) and left it so it can still be adjusted. We cut the rear sight off, smoothed it down and then fully welded a Midwest Industries 2-in-1 rear sight and an Aimpoint/Sparc specific mount. We added a Sparc II onto that which is at the perfect distance from your eye when aiming down the sights. Since it was welded it holds zero once sighted in at your desired range and you can co-witness with it as well. As a backup there are iron sights integrated into the mount that can be used by simply looking through the optic as well. We chose this because it's not resting on any moving parts (i.e. The front rail or rear dust cover) which typically move around and won't hold zero like our mount.Next we added matching Magpul furniture. The front is a modular fore end which has a hundred different attachment options from Magpul's line. Finally we finished it off with a base of Burnt Bronze Cerakote then a thin layer of Graphite Black which was distressed to give it that beautiful (and tactical) war torn look. The gun will also come with an ACE rifle bag, 3-30rd waffle mags, 5-20rd waffle mags and 1,000rds of Wolf 7.62x39 ammo.$1600 for everything or $1400 without the ammo.Please email Nathan@ShueBox.net with any questions or you can call/text to 352-238-6388.Shipping will be a flat $40 (gun and ammo ship separately) or it can be picked up in Tampa, FL.We do accept CC for a 3% fee otherwise money orders or cash (if picking up) is preferred.Gun will need to be shipped to your FFL and can only be shipped to states that allow. If your FFL does not accept shipments from individuals then we have to charge an extra $25 (our actual cost) for our local shop to process and ship this to your FFL.
